result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Nathan R. Kuchenbecker

records.addlTxt: 1:04 PM Prosecuting attorney Lawrence James Lasee in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Nathan R. Kuchenbecker in court, in custody.  Attorney Jon G Spansail in court for Nathan R. Kuchenbecker. Court reviews plea negotiations previously filed doc #18. State request Court to delete repeater. Court removes repeater. Defendant waives reading of count 1 in 22CF125. Court reviews count w/ the defendant and defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST. PQW received/reviewed by the Court w/ defendant. Court finds defendant's waiver to be made freely and voluntarily and accepts waiver. Voting and firearms warnings given. Pursuant to plea negotiations 22CM25 will be dismissed/read-in. Factual basis found. Adjudged guilty. Court orders PSI. Court revokes bond. Defendant remanded to the OCSD to await sentencing.

11:14 AM Prosecuting attorney Lawrence James Lasee in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Nathan R. Kuchenbecker in court, in custody.  Attorney Jon G Spansail in court for Nathan R. Kuchenbecker. Court makes stmt. No court reporter present today. Hearing is being recorded. No objection from counsel or the State to proceed from counsel. Atty Spansail request for his defendant to enter a plea today, however, the Court will not allow to proceed w/ a plea due to no court reporter. Atty Spansail makes stmt re bond modification. Court makes stmt. State objects to the bond request and makes stmt. Stmt by Atty Spansail. Court denies motion to amend bond. Defendant ordered to appear at next hrg. Present bond cont'd.
Plea hearing on August 31, 2022 at 01:00 pm.
